==Critical reception==
According to ''Stagegrade'', the reviews were mixed, with some praising ("fun, beautiful musical") and some panning ("charm-free") the musical.  The latter especially criticized the use of existing songs rather than having an original score. They conclude that this "may be among the most polarizing shows of the current season."<ref>Chaffa, M. [http://stagegrade.com/productions/1403# "Critical Snapshot"]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502210054/http://stagegrade.com/productions/1403%23 |date=May 2, 2014 }}, stagegrade.com, accessed May 2, 2014</ref>
 
[[Ben Brantley]] in his review for ''[[The New York Times]]'', called the musical "occasionally funny but mostly just loud."<ref>Brantley, Ben. [https://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/11/theater/woody-allen-transforms-his-bullets-over-broadway.html?_r=0# "Woody Allen Transforms His 'Bullets Over Broadway'"], ''The New York Times'', April 10, 2014</ref> Elysa Gardner, in her review for ''[[USA Today]]'', commented that the musical has "playful wit and exuberance" and wrote that "'Bullets' offers as much sheer, shameless fun as any show you'll see this season."<ref>Gardner, Elysa. [https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/theater/2014/04/10/broadway-review-bullets-over-broadway/7412981/ " 'Bullets Over Broadway' a sheer, shameless good time"], ''USA Today'', April 10, 2014</ref>

Alexis Soloski, reviewing for ''The Guardian'', praised the way Stroman tells the plot through her choreography and especially noted the staging for Ashmanskas ("lumbering jetés"), Yorke ("brassy thrusts') and the tap numbers for the male ensemble. However, she found that the songs were not well integrated into the story.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2014/apr/11/bullets-over-broadway-musical-review-woody-allen-new-york | title=Woody Allen musical opens with a bang | publisher=[[The Guardian]] | work=theguardian.com | date=April 11, 2014 | accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref><!--  
<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/4beb9584-c009-11e3-bfbc-00144feabdc0.html | title=Woody Allen's stage version of his 1994 movie is well crafted but only intermittently enjoyable | publisher=[[Financial Times]] | work=ft.com | date=April 10, 2014 | accessdate=April 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB20001424052702303603904579492074059755520 | title=Bulletproof on Broadway | publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]] | work=online.wsj.com | date=April 11, 2014 | accessdate=April 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/culture/la-et-cm-bullets-over-broadway-review-20140411,0,6262390.story | title='Bullets Over Broadway' misses the bull's-eye | publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]] | work=latimes.com | date=April 10, 2014 | accessdate=April 30, 2014}}</ref>
-->

